        "value": "A blood sample drawn from a vein. "
      }
    ],
    "packages": [],
    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "What’s the difference between TB Gold and skin test?",
        "answer": "TB Gold is a blood test requiring one visit. It is not affected by BCG vaccine and is more objective than the TST."
      },
      {
        "question": "How accurate is the TB Gold test?",
        "answer": "It has high specificity and good sensitivity, especially useful for BCG-vaccinated people."
      },
      {
        "question": "Does a positive TB Gold test mean I have active TB?",
        "answer": "No. It means you’ve been infected, but further testing is needed to check if it’s active."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need to fast?",
        "answer": "No fasting is required."
      },
      {
        "question": "How long do results take?",
        "answer": "Typically 24–72 hours after sample reaches lab."
      },
      {
        "question": "How much does it cost?",
        "answer": "Please contact Cadabam’s Diagnostics for current pricing."
      },
      {
        "question": "What should I do if the test is positive?",
        "answer": "Follow up with your doctor for chest X-ray and further evaluation."
      }
    ],
